contain more information than they display, and dplyr is designed to help you sort of

00:00:52.080 --> 00:01:02.040
access that information. So, you'll need to run library dplyr before you use the functions

00:01:02.040 --> 00:01:05.400
in this package, and you'll also need to install the package, of course, if you want to use

